' plan-59-E: CONVERTED from `resource-invalidate-not-owner-invalid`.
'
' This fixture used to assert that a `RES` parameter could not be closed by the
' callee (`TYPE_RESOURCE_INVALIDATE_NOT_OWNER`, 2-203-0086 — now retired). Under
' resource-scoped ownership a `RES` is a pointer to the ONE resource and any
' holder may close it; the outermost scope that touches it closes it once if
' nobody already did.
'
' It is kept, not deleted, so what the original protected stays traceable: that
' this shape is DECIDED rather than accidental. Only the verdict changed — it now
' asserts the code compiles.
'
' This is `res.md` §8's headline benefit in miniature: "'Take a handle, give it
' back' becomes writable. Not expressible today in any form."
IMPORT fs

SUB consume(RES f AS File)
  fs::close(f)
END SUB

FUNC main AS Integer
  RES f AS File = fs::createTempFile()
  consume(f)
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
